HEADWORD: Torchon lace
<hw>Tor"chon lace`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F. <ets>torchon</ets> a kind
of coarse napkin.]</ety> <def>a simple thread lace worked upon a pillow
with coarse thread; also, a similar lace made by machinery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

